<paragraph id="94F4B6F2D50FD5D6BE845CBA3E02C797" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="778AFB0095EB99D57720383B2FA9495F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="E9A7F7A546FA79EE07DED52620EAEC79" authorityName="Hongo, Memoirs of Shiga University 18: 50" authorityYear="1968" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Russula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Russula bella" order="Russulales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis id="B0A71127CFA65CFAADCD5EB4C7C2BE5D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Russula bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphological similar to 
<taxonomicName id="9BC8CFFA1E92B2B239EAA69E1FB22FCC" genus="R." lsidName="R. pseudoamoenicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="pseudoamoenicolor">
<emphasis id="8644E5E612735995970D7662E452D20F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">R. pseudoamoenicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="415F1BDF74EA2BF258DA46E7020DC8A6" genus="R." lsidName="R. punicea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="punicea">
<emphasis id="DD197A6C376BE33AA37FB7594BE49757" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">R. punicea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="E0D946F92FA361DCAF3D6CCC70834CFC" genus="R." lsidName="R. violeipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="violeipes">
<emphasis id="F3CCA01680562EACABCCECEB0332FB5A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">R. violeipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="C1703DCE4DDB1E1D7771F3060119D121" authorityName="A. Ghosh, Buyck, K. Das, Baghela &amp; R. P. Bhatt" authorityYear="2016" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Russula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Russula pseudoamoenicolor" order="Russulales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pseudoamoenicolor">
<emphasis id="DF4676E5565273117BFB444C22215579" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Russula pseudoamoenicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a more vividly colored pileus and a larger basidiome and hymenial cystidia than those of 
<taxonomicName id="A065337C00FB81DDEA7D070CD2C54FE6" genus="R." lsidName="R. bella" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis id="7AB436EA7B5EFDB5890EFB2353F5B537" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">R. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="DC7D9ABDC8DE4ECB7B9DBF18B472C916" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-016-0373-x" author="Hyde, KD" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 270" refId="B28" refString="Hyde, KD, Hongsanan, S, Jeewon, R, Bhat, DJ, McKenzie, EHC, Jones, EBG, Phookamsak, R, Ariyawansa, HA, Boonmee, S, Zhao, Q, Abdel-Aziz, FA, Abdel-Wahab, MA, Banmai, S, Chomnunti, P, Cui, B-K, Daranagama, DA, Das, K, Dayarathne, MC, de Silva, NI, Dissanayake, AJ, Doilom, M, Ekanayaka, AH, Gibertoni, TB, Goes-Neto, A, Huang, S-K, Jayasiri, SC, Jayawardena, RS, Konta, S, Lee, HB, Li, W-J, Lin, C-G, Liu, J-K, Lu, Y-Z, Luo, Z-L, Manawasinghe, IS, Manimohan, P, Mapook, A, Niskanen, T, Norphanphoun, C, Papizadeh, M, Perera, RH, Phukhamsakda, C, Richter, C, de Santiago, ALCMA, Drechsler-Santos, ER, Senanayake, IC, Tanaka, K, Tennakoon, TMDS, Thambugala, KM, Tian, Q, Tibpromma, S, Thongbai, B, Vizzini, A, Wanasinghe, DN, Wijayawardene, NN, Wu, H-X, Yang, J, Zeng, X-Y, Zhang, H, Zhang, J-F, Bulgakov, TS, Camporesi, E, Bahkali, AH, Amoozegar, MA, Araujo-Neta, LS, Ammirati, JF, Baghela, A, Bhatt, RP, Bojantchev, D, Buyck, B, da Silva, GA, de Lima, CLF, de Oliveira, RJV, de Souza, CAF, Dai, Y-C, Dima, B, Duong, TT, Ercole, E, Mafalda-Freire, F, Ghosh, A, Hashimoto, A, Kamolhan, S, Kang, J-C, Karunarathna, SC, Kirk, PM, Kytoevuori, I, Lantieri, A, Liimatainen, K, Liu, Z-Y, Liu, X-Z, Luecking, R, Medardi, G, Mortimer, PE, Nguyen, TTT, Promputtha, I, Raj, KNA, Reck, MA, Lumyong, S, Shahzadeh-Fazeli, SA, Stadler, M, Soudi, MR, Su, H-Y, Takahashi, T, Tangthirasunun, N, Uniyal, P, Wang, Y, Wen, T-C, Xu, J-C, Zhang, Z-K, Zhao, Y-C, Zhou, J-L, Zhu, L, 2016. Fungal diversity notes 367-490: taxonomic and phylogenetic contribution to fungal taxa. Fungal Diversity 80 (1): 1 - 270, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-016-0373-x" title="Fungal diversity notes 367 - 490: taxonomic and phylogenetic contribution to fungal taxa." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-016-0373-x" volume="80" year="2016">Hyde et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="199080A5F924A26853F40828615ABDBC" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Russula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Russula punicea" order="Russulales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="punicea">
<emphasis id="0B3B286CF27F38C7C3EC28E725D3CBC4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Russula punicea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="CD39FCAF8EA22C6803395F2E1BEF2099" genus="R." lsidName="R. bella" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis id="5EEEB1FD36C15507BAA17C01714FA8F3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">R. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of hymenial cystidia; the former has acute cystidia, whereas the latter has obtuse cystidia (
<bibRefCitation id="EC3383406CC2544D6EBBE8FB756FC096" author="Chiu, WF" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B15" refString="Chiu, WF, 1945. The Russulaceae of Yunnan. Lloydia 8(1): 31-59." title="The Russulaceae of Yunnan. Lloydia 8 (1): 31 - 59." year="1945">Chiu 1945</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B7A6ECD26EB8B982FE29E9645AF114CD" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/1293963" author="Hongo, T" journalOrPublisher="Memoir of Shiga University" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="47 - 52" refId="B27" refString="Hongo, T, 1968. Notulae Mycologicae (7). Memoir of Shiga University 18: 47 - 52, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/1293963" title="Notulae Mycologicae (7)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/1293963" volume="18" year="1968">Hongo 1968</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="24ECE3F78E963E41FA59E59EEBCD0C57" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Russulaceae" genus="Russula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Russula violeipes" order="Russulales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="violeipes">
<emphasis id="371B1E1360CD218C5CD95E93B0FAE6A5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Russula violeipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="36E718C5B4FA8BCAAB52300B7BBC36FA" genus="R." lsidName="R. bella" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis id="765595C052C8ECEA2055BD4EE797D10F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">R. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the yellowish to greenish smeared violet color of the pileus (
<bibRefCitation id="EA3548AC16CC543F47F1239B3EC25A95" author="Kraenzlin, F" journalOrPublisher="Verlag Mykologia, Luzern" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B32" refString="Kraenzlin, F, 2005. Fungi of Switzerland, vol 6, Russulaceae: Lactarius, Russula. Verlag Mykologia, Luzern" title="Fungi of Switzerland, vol 6, Russulaceae: Lactarius, Russula." year="2005">
<normalizedToken id="5A6ABFA540645A87F49286157734497F" originalValue="Kränzlin">Kraenzlin</normalizedToken>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
). Moreover, 
<emphasis id="53DECFA53CD880E4C371F32607B03659" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
R 
<taxonomicName id="60C9B37996A7BF1F359411C5D00188CD" genus="R." lsidName="violeipes" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="violeipes">violeipes</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has larger basidia (45-65 
<normalizedToken id="852543255B0912DE4206607C20165696" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
11-14 
<normalizedToken id="057CA21D1E5B2DA5C3EC877D6EF4D60D" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) and pleurocystidia (80-115 
<normalizedToken id="CE551A2C250AAB73E9D93C60E85965CB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12-15 
<normalizedToken id="872893E2346D2480422937B260024F23" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) than those of 
<taxonomicName id="A61AC5A0055D231D17660BAECAF8DB91" genus="R." lsidName="R. bella" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="bella">
<emphasis id="6AE04BAC9C2CEFECCD4B8318937A461C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">R. bella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B916D4C4C0CC3DBDD171AD2DA1A65AE8" author="Kraenzlin, F" journalOrPublisher="Verlag Mykologia, Luzern" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B32" refString="Kraenzlin, F, 2005. Fungi of Switzerland, vol 6, Russulaceae: Lactarius, Russula. Verlag Mykologia, Luzern" title="Fungi of Switzerland, vol 6, Russulaceae: Lactarius, Russula." year="2005">
<normalizedToken id="6841442252E27A21430462CAA8FB99A0" originalValue="Kränzlin">Kraenzlin</normalizedToken>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
